definition.value: This is an AE which is the inflammation of a vein and is deep.
This is an AE which is a small local, usually rounded, calcification within a vein.

This is an AE which is part of the complex biological response of portal tract tissues to harmful stimuli, such as pathogens, damaged cells, or irritants, and is a protective response involving immune cells, blood vessels, and molecular mediators.
This is an AE which is a rare finding on radiological exams.
This is an AE which results in venous hypertension with the formation of intra- and extrarenal collaterals and/or the development of gonadal vein reflux.
This is an AE which is the lodging of an renal vein embolus, a blockage-causing piece of material, inside a blood vessel.
This is an AE which has been often reported to be associated with acute decompensated heart failure and, to our knowledge.

This is an AE which is characterized clinically by a local syndrome in an arm, the chest or a leg, by an irregular temperature (toothsaw curve), by blood cultures that are simultaneously or successively positive for one or several pathogenic microorganisms, by repeated, multiple infected embolism and by the possibility of endocarditis as a complication.
This is an AE which is a vein that is close to the surface of the body and is prominent.
This is an AE which is important features of advanced heart failure.
This is an AE which is the build-up of fluid in the visceral  tissue.
This is an AE which is pain that results from the activation of nociceptors of the thoracic, pelvic, or abdominal viscera (organs).
This is an AE which is a prolapse or a sinking of the abdominal viscera (internal organs) below their natural position.
This is an AE which is a group of abnormal heart rhythms (arrhythmias) usually caused by a malfunction of the sinus node, the heart's primary pacemaker.
This is an AE which is an abnormal growth of sinus tissue projecting from a mucous membrane.
This is an AE which is any cardiac rhythm in which depolarisation of the cardiac muscle begins at the sinus node.
This is an AE which is a commonly encountered variation of normal sinus rhythm.
This is an AE which is a form of iron overload disorder resulting in the accumulation of hemosiderin.
This is an AE which indicates accumulation of iron in the body from any cause.

This is an AE which maternal IgG antibodies with specificity for the ABO blood group system pass through the placenta to the fetal circulation where they can cause hemolysis of fetal red blood cells which can lead to fetal anemia and HDN.
This is an AE which is a condition of the mucous membranes characterized by the sudden appearance of one or more blood blisters within the oral cavity.
This is an AE which frequently results in death, prompt treatment may result in full recovery .
This is an AE which can damage the internal capsule and lead to high rates of disability and mortality.

This is an AE which is a type of prediabetes, in which a person's blood sugar levels during fasting are consistently above the normal range, but below the diagnostic cut-off for a formal diagnosis of diabetes mellitus.
This is an AE which is the vomiting of blood.
This is an AE which is blood escaping from the circulatory system from damaged blood vessels and is traumatic .
This is an AE which is the leakage of a fluid out of its container into the surrounding area, especially blood or blood cells from vessels.
This is an AE which refers a generic term for the presence of toxins in the blood caused by bacterial.
This is an AE which is a fall in blood sugar to levels below normal.
This is an AE which is inflammation of the perivascular skin, typically characterized by itchiness, redness and a rash.
This is an AE which related to renal replacement therapy (HIRRT) is a frequent complication of all renal replacement therapy (RRT) modalities commonly used in the intensive care unit.
This is an AE which is a type of blister that forms when subdermal tissues and blood vessels are damaged without piercing the skin.
This is an AE which is a common manifestation of plasma cell disease, and it is sometimes caused by autoimmune diseases (AIDs).
This is an AE which is a disease caused by parasitic flatworms called schistosomes.
This is an AE which is a process of purifying the blood of a person whose kidneys are not working normally.
This is an AE which is a process to prevent and stop bleeding, meaning to keep blood within a damaged blood vessel (the opposite of hemostasis is hemorrhage).
This is an AE which is a rare congenital defect in which the major visceral organs are distributed abnormally within the chest and abdomen.
This is an AE which is a variant of asystole and is usually ventricular in origin.
This is an AE which resulting from dysfunction of the heart.
This is an AE which is the lodging of an embolus, a blockage-causing piece of material, inside a blood vessel.
This is an AE which is a medical condition in which abnormal distribution of blood flow in the smallest blood vessels results in inadequate supply of blood to the body's tissues and organs.
This is an AE which is a type of tissue death caused by a lack of blood supply.
This is an AE which is a medical condition in which the spasm of small arteries causes episodes of reduced blood flow to end arterioles.
This is an AE which is the most common type of ischemic stroke, resulting from the occlusion of small penetrating arteries that provide blood to the brain's deep structures.

This is an AE which is a congenital heart defect where the left atrium (cor triatriatum sinistrum) or right atrium (cor triatriatum dextrum) is subdivided by a thin membrane, resulting in three atrial chambers (hence the name).
This is an AE which is a defect of the bundle branches or fascicles in the electrical conduction system of the heart.
This is an AE which is the leakage of a fluid out of its container into the surrounding area, especially blood or blood cells from vessels.

This is an AE which refers to cardiac arrest in which the electrocardiogram shows a heart rhythm that should produce a pulse, but does not. Pulseless electrical activity is found initially in about 55% of people in cardiac arrest.
